{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Autti's Udacity dataset [88], launched in 2017, is extracted from videos recorded by cameras mounted on vehicles.",
    "These videos have a resolution of 1920x1200 pixels and are divided into two datasets.",
    "The first dataset contains daytime videos of Mountain View, California, and nearby cities, with 9,423 frames and more than 65,000 annotated objects.",
    "The second dataset is similar to the first dataset but contains images with obstacles that make detection more difficult.",
    "This dataset contains more than 15,000 frames, including images taken under different weather conditions, such as sunny and cloudy, increasing the difficulty of object detection.The Vehicle Image Database primarily focuses on vision-based vehicle classification tasks [89]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
